I'm having a similar issue, except I stumbled into it with a regular `podman container run`, trying to use a secret created with the `pass` driver.

```
~ ⌚ 11:25:29
$ podman secret inspect d7cd503c63b22d3daf3bd2a5b --showsecret
[]
Error: inspecting secret: d7cd503c63b22d3daf3bd2a5b: no such secret

~ ⌚ 11:25:31
$ podman secret inspect d7cd503c63b22d3daf3bd2a5b
[
    {
        "ID": "d7cd503c63b22d3daf3bd2a5b",
        "CreatedAt": "2026-04-20T13:34:53.47350634+03:00",
        "UpdatedAt": "2026-04-20T13:34:53.47350634+03:00",
        "Spec": {
            "Name": "topsecret",
            "Driver": {
                "Name": "pass",
                "Options": {}
            },
            "Labels": {}
        }
    }
]
```

I'm not sure if this is related. This is on RHEL 9.7, with podman version 5.6.0.
